comments: Sabonis (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Finney-Smith (DAL).
Finney-Smith (DAL) makes marginal contact with Sabonis (SAC) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) does not extend his off arm from elbow to wrist into Fox's (SAC) body to clear space during the drive.
Fox (SAC) takes fewer than three steps after he has gathered the ball.
Brunson (DAL) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Dinwiddie (DAL) makes contact with Fox's (SAC) body as he gathers and enters his upward shooting motion. The contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie's (DAL) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Brunson (DAL) makes marginal contact with DiVincenzo's (SAC) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Mitchell (SAC) legally contests Brunson's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Bullock (DAL) makes foot to foot contact with Fox (SAC) during his drive, and the contact affects his SQBR.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Finney-Smith (DAL) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Brunson (DAL) legally contests Barnes' (SAC) jump shot attempt.

Barnes (SAC) makes incidental contact to Brunson's (DAL) head/face area with his shooting hand as he is lands following the jump shot. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
